Of course! Here's an example of creating a basic RESTful API using Spring Boot:

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api")
public class SampleController {

    @GetMapping("/hello")
    public String sayHello() {
        return "Hello, World!";
    }
}
```
This API will return the string "Hello, World!" when accessing /api/hello. Would you like me to help you extend its functionality?
